# Coding standards (C / ASM)

## Language choice

- Default to C via MSXgl.
- Use Z80 assembly only for clear size, speed, timing, or hardware-access wins.
- Keep ISR / timing-critical code isolated (for example `src/interrupts.s`).

## Style

- Prefer clear names over abbreviations; match existing project naming.
- Keep functions short; one responsibility per module where practical.
- No host-only libraries in MSX target code.
- Document non-obvious memory layout, I/O ports, and mapper assumptions near the code that depends on them.

## Safety on Z80

- Be explicit about interrupt state around shared data.
- Avoid large stack frames and deep recursion.
- Do not assume uninitialized RAM contents.
- Prefer fixed-point / integer math; document any needed timing assumptions (PAL vs NTSC).

## Headers and generated code

- Project headers live in `include/`.
- Generated sources/includes belong in `generated/` and are rebuilt from `assets/` or tools—do not duplicate them into `src/`.
